    {
      "id": "node-1pjsp7-8",
      "parent": "node-1w18qu-4",
      "title": "Usually our brain need a dumb stash to put ideas or thoughts first and organized later",
      "description": "<p><strong>3 Rules for a Successful Dump</strong></p><ol><li><p><span><strong>Zero Friction:</strong> The stash must be accessible in a single tap or click. No menus, no tags, no filing.</span></p></li><li><p><span><strong>Write Everything:</strong> Dump bad ideas alongside good ones. An unwritten bad idea clogs up your working memory just as much as a great one.</span></p></li><li><p><span><strong>The Review:</strong> Schedule a regular time (daily or weekly) to review your stash and decide what becomes a task, a project, or trash.</span></p></li></ol><p></p>",
      "color": 6,
      "collapsed": false,
